      <h1 class='title'>Bed Occupancy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c274WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_274ws' title='Col. 274WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c274WS' name='column_274ws' href='#column_274ws' rel='bookmark'>274WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06382'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_344'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-burstow' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_344' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul Burstow' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-paul-burstow" title="Mr Paul Burstow">Mr. Burstow</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06382">To ask the Secretary of State for Health what assessment his Department has made of the optimal level of bed occupancy to reduce trolley waits for emergency admissions and cancelled operations. [88561]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06383'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_345'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-lammy' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_345' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Lammy' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-lammy" title="Mr David Lammy">Mr. Lammy</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06383">I refer the hon. Member to the reply I gave to the hon. Member for Epsom and Ewell (Chris Grayling) on <a href="/written_answers/2002/dec/19/assisted-dying#column_1039w">19 December 2002,<span class="italic">Official Report,</span> column 1039W</a>.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06384'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_346'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-chris-grayling' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_346' title='Link to this speech by Mr Chris Grayling' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-chris-grayling" title="Mr Chris Grayling">Chris Grayling</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06384">To ask the Secretary of State for Health what the Government's target is for occupancy levels in<span class="italic">(a)</span> general and <span class="italic">(b)</span> acute NHS beds; and what the levels were in 1997. [87533]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06385'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_347'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-hutton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_347' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Hutton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-hutton" title="Mr John Hutton">Mr. Hutton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06385">The Department has not issued any specific guidance on bed occupancy. As part of routine capacity planning each national health service trust needs to establish the levels of occupancy required for different specialties and types of care depending on their own particular circumstances. Appropriate levels of occupancy will depend on a number of factors including specialty, the balance between emergency and planned admissions and the size of the hospital.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06386">In 1996&#x2013;97 the bed occupancy level for general and acute NHS beds was 80.7 per cent. Over the last two years, the number of beds have increased, reversing a 40 year decline.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
